@title ERC20Interface

nodes.name: ERC20Interface

nodes.documentation: @dev Contract function to receive approval and execute function in one call
nodes.name: ApproveAndCallFallBack

nodes.documentation:
@title Leblock
@dev ERC20 Token, with the addition of symbol, name and decimals and an initial supply
nodes.name: Leblock

nodes.documentation: @dev Constructor

Transfer the balance from token owner's account to `to` account
- Owner's account must have sufficient balance to transfer
- 0 value transfers are allowed
nodes.name: transfer

nodes.documentation:
Token owner can approve for `spender` to transferFrom(...) `tokens`
from the token owner's account

     * https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-20-token-standard.md
recommends that there are no checks for the approval double-spend attack
as this should be implemented in user interfaces
nodes.name: approve

nodes.documentation:
Transfer `tokens` from the `from` account to the `to` account

     * The calling account must already have sufficient tokens approve(...)-d
for spending from the `from` account and
- From account must have sufficient balance to transfer
- Spender must have sufficient allowance to transfer
- 0 value transfers are allowed
nodes.name: transferFrom

nodes.documentation:
Returns the amount of tokens approved by the owner that can be
transferred to the spender's account
nodes.name: allowance

nodes.documentation:
Token owner can approve for `spender` to transferFrom(...) `tokens`
from the token owner's account. The `spender` contract function
`receiveApproval(...)` is then executed
nodes.name: approveAndCall

nodes.documentation: @dev Owner can transfer out any accidentally sent ERC20 tokens
nodes.name: withDrawAnyERC20Token
